article_title: Mead says state missed out on Medicaid opportunity
article_text:
Cheyenne, WY (82001)

Today

Mostly cloudy. A stray shower or thunderstorm is possible. High near 60F. Winds NNE at 10 to 20 mph..

Tonight

Partly cloudy skies. A stray shower or thunderstorm is possible. Low around 40F. Winds WNW at 5 to 10 mph.

article_metadata.news_keywords: , news, local news, matt mead, medicaid, wyoming, revenue
article_metadata.author: Laura Hancock, Casper Star-Tribune

og.description: CASPER – Some of Wyoming’s unemployed energy workers would now be eligible for health coverage if the state had expanded Medicaid to low-income Wyomingites, Gov. Matt Mead said.
